text: I learned today that Houston actually had more inches of rain fall 17 years ago during Tropical Storm Allison than Hurricane Harvey. TS Allison did not cover as wide a space as the hurricane and therefore more widespread devastation. Houston: A River Runs Through It!

RECORD RAINS: @ TravisABC13 breaks down the numbers of Tropical Storm Allison compared to Hurricane Harvey. It was this day 17 years ago that intense rains from Allison bombarded Houston. https://abc13.co/2JDkTjr
